Cantrips						KEY:Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Cantrips						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class Blood Hunter a04c	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul.Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul Lvl 03.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:You learn two cantrips of your choice from the warlock spell list. You learn an additional warlock cantrip of your choice at 10th level.	DEFINE:POOL_Warlock_Cantrip|0	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Warlock_Cantrip|2+(BloodHunterLVL>=10)
Spell Slots						KEY:Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Spell Slots					CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class Blood Hunter a04c	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul.Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul Lvl 03.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The Profane Soul Spellcasting table shows how many spell slots you have. The table also shows what the level of those slots is; all of your spell slots are the same level. To cast one of your warlock spells of 1st level or higher, you must expend a spell slot. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a short or long rest. For example, when you are 8th level, you have two 2nd-level spell slots. To cast the 1st-level spell thunderwave, you must spend one of those slots, and you cast it as a 2nd-level spell.	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=1|BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,3	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=2|BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,7	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=3|BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=4|BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,17	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=1|-BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,7	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=2|-BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLCAST|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=3|-BloodHunterCastSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,17	DEFINE:BloodHunterCastSlotCount|0	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterCastSlotCount|1+(BloodHunter>=5)+(BloodHunter>=14)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterCast0|99	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterCast1|ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=3)-ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=7)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterCast2|ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=7)-ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=11)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterCast3|ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=11)-ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=17)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterCast4|ProfaneSoulSlots*(BloodHunterLVL>=17)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterKnown1|ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=3)-ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=7)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterKnown2|ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=7)-ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=11)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterKnown3|ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=11)-ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=17)	BONUS:VAR|BloodHunterKnown4|ProfaneSoulKnown*(BloodHunterLVL>=17)	DEFINE:ProfaneSoulSlots|0	BONUS:VAR|ProfaneSoulSlots|1+(BloodHunterLVL>=5)+(BloodHunterLVL>=14)	DEFINE:ProfaneSoulKnown|0	BONUS:VAR|ProfaneSoulKnown|2+(BloodHunterLVL>=5)+(BloodHunterLVL>=7)+(BloodHunterLVL>=9)+(BloodHunterLVL>=11)+(BloodHunterLVL>=13)+(BloodHunterLVL>=15)+(BloodHunterLVL>=17)+(BloodHunterLVL>=19)+(BloodHunterLVL>=20)
Spells Known Of 1st Level And Higher	KEY:Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul ~ Spells Known Of 1st Level And Higher	CATEGORY:Special Ability	SORTKEY:Class Blood Hunter a04c	TYPE:Blood Hunter Class Feature.Class Feature.Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul.Blood Hunter Order Of The Profane Soul Lvl 03.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 3rd level, you know two 1st-level spells of your choice from the warlock spell list. The Spells Known column of the Profane Soul table shows when you learn more warlock spells of your choice of 1st level and higher. A spell you choose must be of a level no higher than what's shown in the table's Slot Level column for your level. When you reach 11th level, for example, you learn a new warlock spell, which can be 1st, 2nd, or 3rd level. Additionally, when you gain a level in this class and Order, you can choose one of the warlock spells you know and replace is with another spell from the warlock spell list, which also must be of a level for which you have spell slots. Spellcasting Ability.  Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your warlock spells, so you use your Wisdom whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a warlock spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one. Spell save DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier Spell attack modifier = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=1|BloodHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,3	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=2|BloodHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,8	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=3|BloodHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,11	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=4|BloodHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,18	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=1|-BloodHunterKnownSlotCount|PREVARGTEQ:BloodHunterLVL,8	BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|Class=Blood Hunter;Level=2|-B